Real fun play! had a blast watching you learn and improve! Those are pretty nice parries against the knights! So far its going really well.

1:05:00 ish You pissed off an npc? 2 options. Kill and loot. Or if you want their questline and rewards( new game plus if ever you fail a questline, its just optional loot you may not even use anyway) Find Church of Vows,  Just need a celestial dew and interact with a statue. Its possible to regain favor if you really want it.

2:35:25 Vigor guide is not bad. Vigor hits harder at low level. You prioritize something like str or dex if there is a weapon or armor you want that needs a few more points. Low vigor but high damage builds get one shotted or 2 shot real ez. Yea, sure, git gud. Dont be hit, but that takes time. Plus high dmg is more effectively gained by upgrading the weapon during early game, massive str and dex dmg boost really shines mid game or so. You wont be that behind in damage, and your survivability will be higher. 

Against big, intimidating enemies Typically, you move away if an enemy has more reach,  you cant move in since you will get hit. But with iframes during middle of rolls or start of jumps( more recovery, can become jump attack)... You can move in( need good timing) when they attack, then hit them back( they might even lower their head or somthing, and that is a weakspot) and just roll again and still stay in melee range, vs running away, then running back, then hitting( part of the opening is spent when you move, you land less hits). It is the same concept against a small enemy.
